The paper deals with counting homomorphisms from an input graph to a fixed undirected graph, which is a problem in graph theory. The paper also mentions the strong perfect graph theorem and certain graph algorithms, indicating a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The dichotomy theorem mentioned in the abstract suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of tree-like decompositions in previous dichotomy theorems suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the mention of unbounded treewidth suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.GT).
